org.sbml.jsbml

Class ListOf<T extends SBase>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode
      • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractSBase
        • org.sbml.jsbml.ListOf<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>, TreeNode, SBase, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ListOfMemberConstraint, ListOfObjectives, ListOfWithName

    public class ListOf<T extends SBase>
extends AbstractSBase
implements List<T>
    This list implementation is a Java List that extends AbstractSBase. It represents the listOfxxx XML elements in a SBML file. Unfortunately, there is no way for multiple inheritance in Java.
    Since:
    0.8
    Version:
    $Rev: 2094 $
    Author:
    Nicolas Rodriguez, Marine Dumousseau, Andreas Dräger

      • setDebugMode

        public static void setDebugMode(boolean debugMode)
        Allows you to influence the behavior of the toString() method. If set to true, the whole content of this ListOf is displayed by the toString() method, just like it is done in other List implementations. The default for JSBML, however, is, to only display the ListOf.Type of this list.
        Parameters:
        debugMode - the debugMode to set
